Definition: a massive monument with a square base and four triangular sides
Example: begun by Cheops around 2700 BC as royal tombs in ancient Egypt
Synonyms: adj, all, pointed, pyramidal, pyramidical, verb, contact, pyramid, Great_Pyramid, Pyramids_of_Egypt, memorial, i, Seven_Wonders_of_the_Ancient_World, m, a, massive, monument, with, square, base, and, four, triangular, sides, begun, by, Cheops, around, BC, as, royal, tombs, in, ancient, Egypt
Category: noun.artifact
